verses.text_plain: The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, even the prophecy: the man spake unto Ithiel, even unto Ithiel and Ucal,
verses.verse_html: 1The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, even the prophecy: the man spake unto Ithiel, even unto Ithiel and Ucal,

verses.text_plain: Surely I am more brutish than any man, and have not the understanding of a man.
verses.verse_html: 2Surely I am more brutish than any man, and have not the understanding of a man.

verses.text_plain: I neither learned wisdom, nor have the knowledge of the holy.
verses.verse_html:
3I neither learned wisdom, nor have the knowledge of the holy. ▼
▼ have: Heb. know

verses.text_plain: Who hath ascended up into heaven, or descended? who hath gathered the wind in his fists? who hath bound the waters in a garment? who hath established all the ends of the earth? what is his name, and what is his son’s name, if thou canst tell?
verses.verse_html: 4Who hath ascended up into heaven, or descended? who hath gathered the wind in his fists? who hath bound the waters in a garment? who hath established all the ends of the earth? what is his name, and what is his son’s name, if thou canst tell?

verses.text_plain: Every word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him.
verses.verse_html:
5Every word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him. ▼
▼ pure: Heb. purified

tokens.text: unto them that put their trust

verses.text_plain: Add thou not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar.
verses.verse_html: 6Add thou not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar.

tokens.text: thee, and thou be found a liar

verses.text_plain: Two things have I required of thee; deny me them not before I die:
verses.verse_html:
7Two things have I required of thee; deny me them not before I die: ▼
▼ deny…: Heb. withhold not from me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ deny…: Heb. withhold not from me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ deny…: Heb. withhold not from me

verses.text_plain: Remove far from me vanity and lies: give me neither poverty nor riches; feed me with food convenient for me:
verses.verse_html:
8Remove far from me vanity and lies: give me neither poverty nor riches; feed me with food convenient for me: ▼
▼ convenient…: Heb. of my allowance

footnotes.body_html: ▼ convenient…: Heb. of my allowance

verses.text_plain: Lest I be full, and deny thee, and say, Who is the Lord? or lest I be poor, and steal, and take the name of my God in vain.
verses.verse_html:
9Lest I be full, and deny thee, and say, Who is the Lord? or lest I be poor, and steal, and take the name of my God in vain. ▼
▼ deny…: Heb. belie thee

footnotes.body_html: ▼ deny…: Heb. belie thee

verses.text_plain: Accuse not a servant unto his master, lest he curse thee, and thou be found guilty.
verses.verse_html:
10Accuse not a servant unto his master, lest he curse thee, and thou be found guilty. ▼
▼ Accuse…: Heb. Hurt not with thy tongue

tokens.text: thee, and thou be found guilty

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Accuse…: Heb. Hurt not with thy tongue
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Accuse…: Heb. Hurt not with thy tongue

verses.text_plain: There is a generation that curseth their father, and doth not bless their mother.
verses.verse_html: 11There is a generation that curseth their father, and doth not bless their mother.

verses.text_plain: There is a generation that are pure in their own eyes, and yet is not washed from their filthiness.
verses.verse_html: 12There is a generation that are pure in their own eyes, and yet is not washed from their filthiness.

verses.text_plain: There is a generation, O how lofty are their eyes! and their eyelids are lifted up.
verses.verse_html: 13There is a generation, O how lofty are their eyes! and their eyelids are lifted up.

verses.text_plain: There is a generation, whose teeth are as swords, and their jaw teeth as knives, to devour the poor from off the earth, and the needy from among men.
verses.verse_html: 14There is a generation, whose teeth are as swords, and their jaw teeth as knives, to devour the poor from off the earth, and the needy from among men.

verses.text_plain: The horseleach hath two daughters, crying, Give, give. There are three things that are never satisfied, yea, four things say not, It is enough:
verses.verse_html:
15The horseleach hath two daughters, crying, Give, give. There are three things that are never satisfied, yea, four things say not, It is enough: ▼
▼ It is…: Heb. Wealth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ It is…: Heb. Wealth

verses.text_plain: The grave; and the barren womb; the earth that is not filled with water; and the fire that saith not, It is enough.
verses.verse_html: 16The grave; and the barren womb; the earth that is not filled with water; and the fire that saith not, It is enough.

verses.text_plain: The eye that mocketh at his father, and despiseth to obey his mother, the ravens of the valley shall pick it out, and the young eagles shall eat it.
verses.verse_html:
17The eye that mocketh at his father, and despiseth to obey his mother, the ravens of the valley shall pick it out, and the young eagles shall eat it. ▼
▼ the valley: or, the brook

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the valley: or, the brook

verses.text_plain: There be three things which are too wonderful for me, yea, four which I know not:
verses.verse_html: 18There be three things which are too wonderful for me, yea, four which I know not:

verses.text_plain: The way of an eagle in the air; the way of a serpent upon a rock; the way of a ship in the midst of the sea; and the way of a man with a maid.
verses.verse_html:
19The way of an eagle in the air; the way of a serpent upon a rock; the way of a ship in the midst of the sea; and the way of a man with a maid. ▼
▼ midst: Heb. heart

verses.text_plain: Such is the way of an adulterous woman; she eateth, and wipeth her mouth, and saith, I have done no wickedness.
verses.verse_html: 20Such is the way of an adulterous woman; she eateth, and wipeth her mouth, and saith, I have done no wickedness.

verses.text_plain: For three things the earth is disquieted, and for four which it cannot bear:
verses.verse_html: 21For three things the earth is disquieted, and for four which it cannot bear:

verses.text_plain: For a servant when he reigneth; and a fool when he is filled with meat;
verses.verse_html: 22For a servant when he reigneth; and a fool when he is filled with meat;

verses.text_plain: For an odious woman when she is married; and an handmaid that is heir to her mistress.
verses.verse_html: 23For an odious woman when she is married; and an handmaid that is heir to her mistress.

verses.text_plain: There be four things which are little upon the earth, but they are exceeding wise:
verses.verse_html:
24There be four things which are little upon the earth, but they are exceeding wise: ▼
▼ exceeding…: Heb. wise, made wise

footnotes.body_html: ▼ exceeding…: Heb. wise, made wise

verses.text_plain: The ants are a people not strong, yet they prepare their meat in the summer;
verses.verse_html: 25The ants are a people not strong, yet they prepare their meat in the summer;

verses.text_plain: The conies are but a feeble folk, yet make they their houses in the rocks;
verses.verse_html: 26The conies are but a feeble folk, yet make they their houses in the rocks;

verses.text_plain: The locusts have no king, yet go they forth all of them by bands;
verses.verse_html:
27The locusts have no king, yet go they forth all of them by bands; ▼
▼ by…: Heb. gathered together

footnotes.body_html: ▼ by…: Heb. gathered together

verses.text_plain: The spider taketh hold with her hands, and is in kings’ palaces.
verses.verse_html: 28The spider taketh hold with her hands, and is in kings’ palaces.

verses.text_plain: There be three things which go well, yea, four are comely in going:
verses.verse_html: 29There be three things which go well, yea, four are comely in going:

verses.text_plain: A lion which is strongest among beasts, and turneth not away for any;
verses.verse_html: 30A lion which is strongest among beasts, and turneth not away for any;

verses.text_plain: A greyhound; an he goat also; and a king, against whom there is no rising up.
verses.verse_html:
31A greyhound; an he goat also; and a king, against whom there is no rising up. ▼
▼ greyhound: or, horse: Heb. girt in the loins

footnotes.body_text: ▼ greyhound: or, horse: Heb. girt in the loins
footnotes.body_html: ▼ greyhound: or, horse: Heb. girt in the loins

verses.text_plain: If thou hast done foolishly in lifting up thyself, or if thou hast thought evil, lay thine hand upon thy mouth.
verses.verse_html: 32If thou hast done foolishly in lifting up thyself, or if thou hast thought evil, lay thine hand upon thy mouth.

tokens.text: thyself, or if thou hast thought evil

verses.text_plain: Surely the churning of milk bringeth forth butter, and the wringing of the nose bringeth forth blood: so the forcing of wrath bringeth forth strife.
verses.verse_html: 33Surely the churning of milk bringeth forth butter, and the wringing of the nose bringeth forth blood: so the forcing of wrath bringeth forth strife.
